Below are frequently asked questions related to the rollout of the Atlas One system. If you have any questions that are not answered below, please contact us directly.

longDescription.en-US: Atlas One is an enterprise public safety platform brought to you by the team behind MobilePD. Over the last 10 years, we have built approximately  100 communication platforms for local and state public safety government agencies across North America.  Our experience has led us from our legacy platform to a new global enterprise system.  In light of the COVID-19 crisis, we have accelerated our implementation plan so we can assist communities in North America and around the world.

title.en-US: How did you build this so quickly?

longDescription.en-US: We have spent the last three years building Atlas One. Although our plan was to launch Atlas One in April as a public safety platform, with the worldwide outbreak of COVID-19, we realized what we have built is in fact a premier public health communication platform. We have accelerated the launch of Atlas One, and our entire team is working around the clock.

title.en-US: How much does Atlas One cost?

longDescription.en-US: Due to the worldwide outbreak of COVID-19, every local, state, and federal health and safety agency can utilize the core Atlas One Alerting and geo-fencing platform for free. We are committed to helping any way we can and we believe providing Atlas One for free is the right thing to do.

title.en-US: How long will Atlas One be free?

longDescription.en-US: The core Atlas One public alerting system will remain available at no cost as a regular feature of the platform even after we recover from the current COVID-19 pandemic. This is part of our commitment to helping make the world a safer place. However, there may be features, including optional premium features, that can be added in addition to the core alert system. If ongoing funding is a concern, please contact us for optional premium feature pricing. Transparency is a primary goal of this program.

title.en-US: When will Atlas One be available?

longDescription.en-US: The Atlas One primary alerting (public mass notification & geo-fencing platform) as well as our content publishing (ability to publish guides, locations of clinics, link to government resources, etc.) features will be available on March 19th. We are working night and day to add additional features, such as private group-based communication, in the coming weeks.

title.en-US: What is the process to enroll my agency?

longDescription.en-US: To enroll your agency in the free Atlas One COVID-19 program, please click here. Once you fill out the application, a member of our team will contact you and schedule an online onboarding training session. Enrollment is first come first serve, and we estimate we can onboard 15-20 agencies/day.

description.en-US: Atlas One has a plan thats right for your organization.

longDescription.en-US:
Atlas One is a new public safety and health communication tool brought to you by the team behind MobilePD. We have dedicated the last ten years to improving public safety outcomes by enhancing each of our local government customers ability to communicate with their residents. We believe transparency and communication are the foundation of a healthy society, and in our current climate, this is more important than ever.

Ten years ago, our team developed the first-ever mobile app for a police department, allowing local public safety to improve communication with the community. Hence, our company name - MobilePD. To date, we have worked with governments from coast to coast, and our software has saved countless lives across North America.

We have spent the last three years laser-focused on our new platform, Atlas One. Our goal has been simple but ambitious: build the most advanced public safety communication platform ever. Through steadfast dedication, our entire team has remained resolute in accomplishing that goal. We are thrilled to announce that Atlas One is now available.

Although we planned to launch Atlas One in the coming months as a public safety platform, with the worldwide outbreak of COVID-19, we realized what we have built is actually a premier public health communication platform. We feel that we have a moral obligation to distribute Atlas One to the worlds health organizations as quickly as possible. To this end, our entire team has been working night and day to repurpose Atlas One as a public health communication system to help educate and prepare communities so they can better respond to this pandemic.

As a testament to our commitment, we will be providing the core Atlas One platform to every local, state, and federal government globally for free. The stakes are too high for any other approach, and we fundamentally believe that this is the right thing to do.

Stay safe.


Team Atlas One
